Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.06,0:00:07.82,Signs,,0,0,0,,Torada House
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.48,0:00:12.07,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Death bu massive hemorrhaging resulting\Nfrom trauma along the whole body.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.61,0:00:13.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did he die from a fall?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.95,0:00:18.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, my only heir and son, Yoshirou was...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.58,0:00:23.75,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)}Torada Naonobu (61)\NHead of the Torada Family
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.91,0:00:23.75,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Struck by the ruthless hand of the demons who\Nbear resentment against our Torada family.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.75,0:00:28.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean somebody shoved him off from some high place?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.21,0:00:30.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it was a tornado.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.51,0:00:33.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My son got caught in a tornado.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.38,0:00:37.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was sucked up into the air and thrown\Ndown to his death in a rocky area.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.89,0:00:40.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A tornado?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.68,0:00:43.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he wasn't murdered by someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.77,0:00:46.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look closely, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-dono{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.94,0:00:49.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you see something in the pool of blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.19,0:00:54.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can see it if you look very carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.90,0:00:57.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something that shouldn't be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.45,0:01:02.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A centipede!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.75,0:01:09.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That centipede corpse appears to have been placed there\Nafter it had been stepped on, but before the blood was dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.17,0:01:12.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, that means some person...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.43,0:01:19.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Despite finding my son in that condition...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.47,0:01:23.10,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Didn't call for help, but, as if saying he deserved what he got...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.85,0:01:28.35,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(210,0)} Torada Tatsue (58)\NNaonobu's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.10,0:01:28.44,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Put that repulsive insect next to to him and left him to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.61,0:01:32.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But maybe it was a centipede corpse that somebody had stepped on...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.61,0:01:35.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the wind of the tornado blew it there by coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.74,0:01:39.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shigetsugu, who was the one who found the body, said this to us:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.12,0:01:41.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"There aren't any centipedes like that in the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.12,0:01:44.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"My brother was left here to die."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.29,0:01:45.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.62,0:01:48.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you say earlier that the deceased was your only heir?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.79,0:01:54.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A moron like him who spends all his time\Non some imaginary buried treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.80,0:01:57.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I no longer consider him to be my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.43,0:02:01.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, you have an idea who the culprit was, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.05,0:02:03.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said someone resented you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.06,0:02:04.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.72,0:02:10.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, the ones who have been feuding with our Torada\Nfamily for countless years —\hthe Tatsuo family.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.15,0:02:16.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fiend who left my son to die must be one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.08,0:02:30.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The curtain rises on a mysterious new era.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.88,0:02:32.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Monday 7:00 reasoning show.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.75,0:02:34.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shingen's treasure! The riddle of the Fuurinkazan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.92,0:02:36.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sound of Ran and Kazuha's screams!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.92,0:02:38.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.55,0:02:40.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.34,0:02:42.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.99,0:04:27.37,Signs,,0,0,0,,Tatsuo House
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.11,0:04:30.20,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,So your son Koiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was not only tied up but buried in the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.58,0:04:33.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then he was beaten to death by being\Nrepeatedly stuck in the head with a blunt weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.87,0:04:36.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On top of that, before his blood had dried...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.63,0:04:39.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone placed the corpse of a centipede\Nnext to him and made their escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.46,0:04:43.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez, this was really cruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.38,0:04:46.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, what did the police say?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.72,0:04:50.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for them, all they do is repeat the same response.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.60,0:04:57.98,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,250)}Tatsuo Tamefumi (56)\NHead of the Tatsuo Family
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.77,0:04:52.73,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,We're still investigating, we're still investigating,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.02,0:04:56.02,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's why I called for you, Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.31,0:04:59.86,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I had my old friend Otaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} from the Osaka police ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.65,0:05:04.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Otaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-han{\r} told me it seems you've\Nalready figured out the culprit's motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.57,0:05:06.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, well, as for the motive...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.74,0:05:09.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was revenge!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.16,0:05:15.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thinking that the death of their own son\Nwas the fault of our Tatsuo family...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.33,0:05:18.29,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,They murdered Kouji in thoughtless retaliation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.33,0:05:21.21,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(270,0)} Tatsuo Shigeyo (78)\NTamefumi's Mother
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.79,0:05:21.21,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Someone from the Torada family, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.63,0:05:24.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mother, we still don't know if that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.88,0:05:29.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The way he was murdered was so malicious, how\Ncan there be any doubt it was them who did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.80,0:05:32.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, who was it that found the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.18,0:05:36.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was my other son, Akira.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.73,0:05:39.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He discovered it on the way home\Nfrom this horseback archery practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.86,0:05:43.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Horseback archery is where you shoot with a\Nbow and arrow while riding on a horse, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.28,0:05:47.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Akira is the top practitioner of it in our village.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.82,0:05:50.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whenever we have our festival, he always demonstrates the technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.33,0:05:54.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where is Akira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.17,0:06:09.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Every one a bullseye! I knew you could do it, Akira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.34,0:06:16.10,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)} Tatsuo Akira (32)\NTamefumi's Son
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.43,0:06:16.23,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I guess with this I'll get to be the horseback\Narchery bowman at the next festival too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.43,0:06:22.06,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(220,0)} Tatsuo Ayaka (27)\NAkira's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.73,0:06:18.69,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,If that happens, it will be the 6th year in a row.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.77,0:06:22.27,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,They should just declare you to be the\Nhorseback archery bowman already.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.57,0:06:27.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no. I haven't reached my senpai's level yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.53,0:06:30.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me. Are you Akira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.74,0:06:31.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.91,0:06:36.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Mouri Kogoro, a detective from Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.91,0:06:42.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's all right with you, I'd like to ask you about the\Nsituation when you discovered Kouji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.50,0:06:45.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, I guess I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.67,0:06:48.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there a reason that would make it difficult to answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.88,0:06:53.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, it's just that someone asked\Nme the exact same thing a bit ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.05,0:06:55.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A boy detective with an Osaka accent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.14,0:06:57.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An Osaka accent?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.68,0:06:59.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Boy detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.56,0:07:01.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It couldn't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.23,0:07:06.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I was the one who found my brother Yoshirou's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.36,0:07:10.07,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(210,0)}Torada Shigetsugu (31)\NNaonobu's Son
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.65,0:07:10.11,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's true that there was the corpse of a centipede next to the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.36,0:07:12.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why a centipede?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.62,0:07:13.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.91,0:07:17.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does either your Torada family or the Tatsuo family...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.08,0:07:19.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have any sort of connection with centipedes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.21,0:07:23.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no real connection, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.04,0:07:26.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I do remember seeing a drawing of a centipede at the festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.84,0:07:27.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Festival?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.05,0:07:30.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that festival where they have the horseback archery...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.51,0:07:33.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The men of the village have a make-believe battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.14,0:07:36.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when they put on that armor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.10,0:07:42.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, you can call it armor, but it's just a fairly lightweight\Nthing made out of plastic that the village provides.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.98,0:07:48.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have the feeling that I've seen it somewhere\Nat that festival, the picture of a centipede.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.61,0:07:51.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where was it? Was it drawn on a chest protector or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.78,0:07:56.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was a dragonfly, I think there was a warlord\Nduring the Sengoku who had one on his helmet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.87,0:08:02.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of warlords, there was a detective who\Ncame by and asked the same questions as you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.79,0:08:03.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.83,0:08:06.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he was a detective from Tokyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.34,0:08:09.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His family name was the same as one of those warlords.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.42,0:08:11.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it have been Mouri?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.51,0:08:13.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right! Mouri like in Mouri Motonari.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.22,0:08:16.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s father!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.26,0:08:19.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, was there a little boy with glasses there too?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.56,0:08:24.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he was asking about the incident\Nmore diligently than the detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.15,0:08:26.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heh, it's Kudo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.23,0:08:32.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That reminds me, Akira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was telling us that a\Nperson died six years ago from a strange accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.24,0:08:33.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.90,0:08:41.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the deceased was the one selected to be our horseback\Narchery bowman at the festival up until that year, Kai Kuroto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.08,0:08:45.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What I heard was that he fell off a cliff while practicing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.58,0:08:48.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who would know more information about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.13,0:08:50.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe my late brother's wife, Yui{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.92,0:08:53.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was the one who found the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.67,0:08:55.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where would she be now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.34,0:08:57.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you see those stables behind the fence?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.18,0:09:02.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She might be taking care of the horses around this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.02,0:09:07.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Kudo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.77,0:09:10.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kudo's been seduced here by the scent of this case too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.94,0:09:16.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This shows what I've always thought, that you and I\Nare two of a kind, like badgers from the same hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.32,0:09:20.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C'mon, give me a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.49,0:09:22.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm still trying to get over the death of my husband!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.87,0:09:25.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't want to try to remember\Nsomething that happened six years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.33,0:09:25.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? Now you're\Ncooking!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.75,0:09:26.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please leave already!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.46,0:09:30.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! You'll have to forgive me for being so...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.96,0:09:35.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.01,0:09:38.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.64,0:09:44.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know a detective with swept-back hair,\Na tiny mustache, and a stupid-looking face?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.31,0:09:49.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By swept-back hair, tiny mustache, and stupid-looking face...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.31,0:09:52.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you mean mine?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.40,0:09:56.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, not at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.45,0:10:00.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}! Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! It's been a longtime!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.20,0:10:02.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}! Have you been doing good?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.49,0:10:03.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.25,0:10:09.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heh, I knew it'd be him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.67,0:10:10.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.84,0:10:13.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's this evil-looking man?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.88,0:10:15.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.51,0:10:19.09,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I'm the one in charge of this case...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.38,0:10:23.51,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)}Yamato Kansuke (35)\NNagano Prefectural\NPolice Detective
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.26,0:10:22.81,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Yamato Kansuke of the Nagano prefectural police.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.27,0:10:25.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A police detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.77,0:10:29.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just asking this lady some questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.86,0:10:35.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK, ma'am, I'll ask you one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.53,0:10:38.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was that thing there six years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.53,0:10:39.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.82,0:10:42.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't I just say I wasn't in the mood to answer you now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.62,0:10:45.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,People's lives are at stake!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.70,0:10:47.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll answer me without any arguments!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.29,0:10:52.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.67,0:11:03.47,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)} Torada Yui (29)\NYoshirou's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.76,0:11:00.93,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,There wasn't any centipede corpse near the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.59,0:11:06.68,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,There was just the dead horse in a pile along with his emaciated body.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.14,0:11:09.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.85,0:11:12.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to have bothered you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.36,0:11:16.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.11,0:11:20.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning behind those centipedes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.65,0:11:22.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I still can't say for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.16,0:11:26.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if we don't figure out this critical point soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.37,0:11:30.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's inevitable that we'll find ourselves rolling in dead bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.00,0:11:37.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like on the battlefields of the Sengoku wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.93,0:11:51.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now for what these two successive cases share in common...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.19,0:11:54.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The people who discovered the bodies\Nwere both related to victims and...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.15,0:11:59.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For some unknown reason, the corpses of\Ncentipedes were placed next to the bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.74,0:12:06.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thing that's bothering me is the incident six years\Nago where, while practicing his horseback archery...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.12,0:12:10.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kai Kuroto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} fell to his death from a cliff along with his horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.04,0:12:13.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd say that was just an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.42,0:12:16.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It probably doesn't have anything to do with these two incidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.54,0:12:21.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, since there were no centipedes or anything next to his corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.05,0:12:25.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is if we believe Torada Yui{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s story.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.34,0:12:26.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.18,0:12:29.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There wasn't anything there like a centipede, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.72,0:12:32.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for the issue of someone leaving him there to die...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.48,0:12:35.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It might just be the same as the first incident where my husband died.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.02,0:12:37.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone left him to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.44,0:12:40.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you say he died instantly when he fell from the cliff?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.07,0:12:44.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did mention it' didn't I? That his corpse was emaciated?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.95,0:12:47.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true that when he fell from the cliff...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.37,0:12:50.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He sustained serious injuries when his\Nbody struck the trees and the rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.70,0:12:53.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His white undershirt became covered in blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.21,0:12:55.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It even became pitch black due to oxidation, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.17,0:12:57.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He starved to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.25,0:12:58.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Starved to death?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.67,0:12:59.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.09,0:13:02.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His hip had been broken and he couldn't stand up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.97,0:13:06.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On that day, the sun didn't strike the place where he fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.30,0:13:09.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was right below the cliff, where people wouldn't normally pass by.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.39,0:13:12.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I discovered him, almost a week had passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.02,0:13:14.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A week?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.89,0:13:18.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though it wasn't just him and his horse had fallen there too...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.15,0:13:19.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nobody found them?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.98,0:13:21.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was there a proper search?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.74,0:13:23.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We searched!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.86,0:13:26.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both the police and the villagers even gave up their sleeping time!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.20,0:13:30.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Officer Kai was loved by everyone in the village!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.66,0:13:31.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.91,0:13:33.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was a policeman?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.70,0:13:36.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. He worked at the village police box.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.96,0:13:40.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had a strong sense of justice, and he was kind and gentle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.50,0:13:44.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You couldn't find anyone in the village\Nwho had anything bad to say about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.55,0:13:47.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why, when he disappeared, the\Nwhole village looked for him frantically!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.09,0:13:51.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Despite that, how could it take a week to find him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.93,0:13:53.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the leaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.18,0:13:53.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The leaves?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.31,0:13:57.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, he'd been buried in leaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.02,0:14:00.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was hidden under them until the wind blew them off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.81,0:14:05.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My brother Yoshirou's body had fallen in a\Nrocky area where the visibility was good...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.24,0:14:06.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he was discovered easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.95,0:14:09.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did everyone in the village look for him right away then too?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.16,0:14:10.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.24,0:14:15.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We started searching when it was almost dawn\Nand we realized my brother hadn't come back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.00,0:14:17.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Started searching?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.12,0:14:22.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean you didn't discover my husband's body\Nby chance on the way to that hole of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.46,0:14:24.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.51,0:14:26.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That hole?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.67,0:14:28.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just a hobby.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.84,0:14:30.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I pretend I'm hunting for treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.10,0:14:33.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You call that a hobby?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.47,0:14:36.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As if it wasn't enough that you don't work,\Nyou're obsessed over something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.23,0:14:39.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You bring shame on the Torada family!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.44,0:14:42.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please be practical, Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.06,0:14:45.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the only heir left to our family.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.78,0:14:50.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, have you discovered anything, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-dono{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.57,0:14:55.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I've only found that next to the body\Nof Kouji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from the Tatsuo family...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.37,0:14:59.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The corpse of a centipede had been placed, just like with Yoshirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.17,0:15:01.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of Kouji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.92,0:15:05.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He used to have a lot of private conversations\Nwith my husband before he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.25,0:15:06.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Private conversations?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.59,0:15:10.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think he would say "Let's go"\Nor "Let's not go" or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.34,0:15:12.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I heard him say that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.80,0:15:19.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said they should go together and see that\None-eyed detective, Yamato, before too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.23,0:15:23.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that since it might be a big deal,\Nwould he please resolve himself to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.40,0:15:24.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.44,0:15:26.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you ask what they were going to him for?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.19,0:15:30.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he just said he couldn't say yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.16,0:15:35.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we should go check with the Tatsuo\Nfamily; they might know something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.45,0:15:37.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, let's strike while the iron is hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.66,0:15:41.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, we'll head over there for a bit and come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.08,0:15:43.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha, you and she can stay and mind the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.21,0:15:45.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can come with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.96,0:15:49.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot, if you come you'll just be in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.80,0:15:58.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They planned to go to the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.35,0:16:01.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My son Kouji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} along with Yoshirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} from the Torada family?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.69,0:16:05.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. You didn't hear anything about this from your son?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.77,0:16:07.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.48,0:16:13.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just that, when Yoshirou kun died, it seemed\Nlike he became frightened of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.32,0:16:15.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Frightened?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.91,0:16:20.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. Even during meals he would\Nbe withdrawn and mutter to himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.41,0:16:24.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Next time it might be my turn to be killed."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.25,0:16:27.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"To killed by the curse."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.05,0:16:29.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C-Curse?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.42,0:16:30.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.59,0:16:35.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The curse of the Torada family who have\Nhated our Tatsuo family for generations!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.85,0:16:41.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, why are their family and yours on such bad terms?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.39,0:16:44.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.23,0:16:47.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A long time ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.74,0:16:54.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, what was it again?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.66,0:16:55.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.20,0:16:56.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Old lady...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.82,0:17:01.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ever since I was a child I've heard that the Torada family hates us...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.91,0:17:03.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I've forgotten why.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.25,0:17:07.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure that's what the people from the Torada family think too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.50,0:17:10.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But now those chains are falling away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.84,0:17:15.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayaka and I have gotten along well with\NYoshirou and Shigetsugu from the Torada family.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.88,0:17:20.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, before they died, those two said\Nthey were going to go to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.85,0:17:24.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could that have been in connection\Nwith that policeman, Kai's, accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.52,0:17:25.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was just an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.94,0:17:29.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After practicing his horse archery...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.02,0:17:31.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must have been exhausted and fallen from the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.03,0:17:36.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He missed a target at the festival that year and was upset about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.53,0:17:38.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, haven't you given that up yet, Ayaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.62,0:17:40.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's what everyone said.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.53,0:17:42.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe due to the shock of having missed...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.49,0:17:44.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He jumped off the cliff on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.75,0:17:47.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't people miss sometimes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.04,0:17:48.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, on occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.92,0:17:52.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} never missed, not even once.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.84,0:17:56.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At least not until the last shot at that year's festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.09,0:18:00.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man would never have committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.64,0:18:03.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A minor embarrassment at the festival...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.06,0:18:10.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wasn't some fool who would abandon the villagers\Nand escape into the other world over something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.11,0:18:16.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? You're staying over there tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.53,0:18:19.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you're not coming back, Heiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.62,0:18:22.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the rain's becoming really nasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.78,0:18:25.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's dangerous to take the mountain roads at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.58,0:18:27.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.87,0:18:30.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't sleep with your belly button showing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.38,0:18:31.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, watch it, Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.63,0:18:34.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He hung up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.59,0:18:36.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think, Kudo?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.88,0:18:38.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you figure something out?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.51,0:18:40.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, nothing yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.22,0:18:46.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm still stuck on what Kouji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was muttering before he was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.93,0:18:49.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Next time it might be my turn—"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.94,0:18:54.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It that was true, then these are serial murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.48,0:18:59.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what's more, there may be more victims to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.87,0:19:07.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.00,0:19:09.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.04,0:19:12.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you hear a strange noise?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.88,0:19:18.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't hear anything except the rain and the thunder.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.05,0:19:20.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen, you can hear that noise alongside them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.22,0:19:23.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sounds like the floor creaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.46,0:19:57.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I said I'm telling you the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.21,0:19:59.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right? Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} saw it too!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.30,0:20:02.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it wasn't a dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.93,0:20:04.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But still...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.47,0:20:07.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha, what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.14,0:20:09.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Heiji! I really saw it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.43,0:20:11.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saw what?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.39,0:20:14.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought I saw it during the lightning flashes last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.98,0:20:17.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was standing right there on the other side of the shoji screen!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.61,0:20:19.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was an armored...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.49,0:20:21.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fugitive warrior!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.20,0:20:23.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A fugitive warrior?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.95,0:20:28.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it possibly have been the armor from\NShigetsugu's room that's used for the festival?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.37,0:20:30.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.50,0:20:33.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because there was a long\Nfringe of hair attached to the helmet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.17,0:20:38.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's like the Suwa-style helmets used by Takeda Shingen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.04,0:20:41.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's Takeda, it could be one of\NTakeda's "Akazomae." (red armored warriors)
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.26,0:20:45.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, that armor, was it red?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.22,0:20:51.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I could only see the silhouette.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.40,0:20:58.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,NO!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.23,0:21:03.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Ayaka locked herself in the restroom and won't come out?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.86,0:21:06.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just after someone mentioned the red armor of Takeda Shingen?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.87,0:21:07.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Aya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.91,0:21:10.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry and come get her, she's being a bother!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.74,0:21:12.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}! Aya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.96,0:21:17.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.92,0:21:20.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's not here, is she? My daughter-in-law isn't here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.92,0:21:22.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.55,0:21:24.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure she was here until just a moment ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.72,0:21:28.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She asked us to leave her alone for a while, so we went away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.97,0:21:33.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She ought to still be in the area, so let's all split up and search for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.52,0:21:35.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK, I'll use my scooter.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.73,0:21:36.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go in my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.40,0:21:40.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Yui{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and I can ride the horses.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.40,0:21:42.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone else will go by foot!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.15,0:21:44.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.61,0:21:46.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.66,0:21:48.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.99,0:21:49.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.16,0:21:52.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayaka! Ayaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.45,0:21:54.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Answer us!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.37,0:21:56.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.37,0:21:58.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.67,0:21:59.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.75,0:22:02.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If only I had been faster...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.14,0:22:10.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This wouldn't have happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.39,0:22:13.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, you shouldn't be—
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.23,0:22:20.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.11,0:22:21.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Has something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.23,0:22:24.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s... Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.24,0:22:26.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.53,0:22:27.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.90,0:22:28.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stay back!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.66,0:22:33.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From here on, this place is under police jurisdiction!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.24,0:22:36.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You all need to stay back!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.29,0:22:38.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.58,0:22:43.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you there, woman on the black horse...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.21,0:22:44.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.84,0:22:45.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.30,0:22:48.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.34,0:22:52.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What on earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.14,0:22:54.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.61,0:23:02.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.52,0:23:06.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Uehara, tell me the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.94,0:23:07.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.36,0:23:09.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,8:59.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.28,0:23:13.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, it's an old habit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.66,0:23:16.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.20,0:23:18.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An old...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.29,0:23:19.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Habit?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.96,0:23:21.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.00,0:23:23.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's been an incident in the woods near the Torada mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.42,0:23:25.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bring the forensics team here immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.88,0:23:29.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right. There's been another serial murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.51,0:23:31.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Serial murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.39,0:23:37.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly. The time Torada Yoshirou was left to die\Nafter bring seriously injured by the tornado...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.22,0:23:39.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was the first incident!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.98,0:23:45.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The time Tatsuo Kouji was tied up, buried\Nin the ground, and beaten to death...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.44,0:23:46.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was the second incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.98,0:23:51.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like what happened in those two incidents...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.61,0:23:55.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just underneath where Tatsuo Ayaka is suspended...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.12,0:23:57.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is the corpse of a centipede!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.70,0:23:58.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.00,0:24:01.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.16,0:24:06.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the area around the body, on top of\Nthe ground that's muddy from the rain...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.17,0:24:10.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right now, there are only my footprints and the marks of my cane.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.38,0:24:15.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, on this tree she was hung from after it rained...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.18,0:24:19.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is absolutely no trace of anyone having climbed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.89,0:24:21.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is an...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.98,0:24:24.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.15,0:24:27.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An impossible crime, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.03,0:24:39.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An impossible crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.87,0:24:46.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it could also be the case that your footprints\Nwhere here already before you brought down the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.67,0:24:50.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that right? Mr. Detective who arrived here awfully quickly?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.01,0:24:58.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I went to the Torada house, they told me everyone\Nhad gone to the woods to search for Tatsuo Ayaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.10,0:24:59.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I just came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.39,0:25:02.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wasn't your timing a little too good?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.93,0:25:08.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Almost like you invited Ayaka san out here by calling\Nher cellphone while she was in the restroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.11,0:25:11.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Put her to sleep, and after making it look like a suicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.07,0:25:14.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Went on to the Torada house, acting all innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.11,0:25:16.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.24,0:25:21.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw the ground before the detective took Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} down, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.45,0:25:25.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were no footprints or cane marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.58,0:25:30.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Putting that aside, I heard that before she locked\Nherself in the restroom, she'd been acting strangely.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.63,0:25:31.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.46,0:25:36.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Last night, on the other side of the shoji screen\Nfrom the room where we were sleeping...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.80,0:25:38.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We saw the silhouette of an armored warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.89,0:25:42.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we said it looked like it was wearing a Suwa-style helmet...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.31,0:25:44.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suddenly Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} got all scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.98,0:25:46.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.44,0:25:53.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murderous curse caused by provoking Lord Shingen's wrath.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.28,0:25:57.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That centipede corpse is the clear evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.95,0:26:02.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does a centipede have to do with Takeda Shingen?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.45,0:26:03.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.95,0:26:10.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lord Shingen called the people who worked as\Nrunners on the battlefield "The Centipedes."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.92,0:26:14.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They would carry centipede flags at their backs.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.38,0:26:15.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.97,0:26:19.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew I'd seen a picture of a centipede somewhere before.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.30,0:26:23.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw someone wearing that flag during the festival competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.85,0:26:27.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How can you be going treasure hunting\Nwithout even knowing something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.23,0:26:33.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you mean that treasure you\Nmentioned is really Takeda Shingen's?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.32,0:26:37.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Shingen's hidden gold mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.11,0:26:40.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even since he found some books and maps\Nin our cellar that seemed to refer to it...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.74,0:26:43.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s been crazy about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.20,0:26:47.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those two who died earlier along with Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.46,0:26:53.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And even Tatsuo Akira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} here all got dragged into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.50,0:26:56.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We weren't doing it for selfish reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.55,0:26:59.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We thought if we really found it, it would help revitalize the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.43,0:27:04.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But still, why did Ayaka have to be cursed too?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.22,0:27:07.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All she did was bring refreshments for us at the mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.39,0:27:10.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not a curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.69,0:27:13.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a full-fledged murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.07,0:27:16.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just like the detective with the mustache said.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.82,0:27:20.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsuo Ayaka had her cellphone here in her waist pouch.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.57,0:27:24.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While she was secluding herself in the restroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.74,0:27:29.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was fooled into coming out by the serial murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.41,0:27:32.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, if you don't want to us to be finding your corpse...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.46,0:27:34.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't go wandering around alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.50,0:27:41.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Especially you two who have been searching for buried gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.93,0:27:50.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really? That armored warrior was really standing right here?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.02,0:27:53.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but he left right away though.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.69,0:27:58.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you just open up the shoji\Nscreen and flatten him with your karate?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.40,0:28:01.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because! I thought it was a ghost so it wouldn't have a real body!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.99,0:28:04.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you're opponent is a ghost, stuff like karate\Nand aikido will just pass right through them.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.12,0:28:07.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot, there's no such thing as ghosts in this—
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.08,0:28:11.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know what this is, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.17,0:28:16.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's looks like unraveled threads of the vinyl cord that\Nyou sometimes use on packages, but so what?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.21,0:28:19.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Several pieces of it had fallen along the corridor and on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.88,0:28:20.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.13,0:28:25.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If these thin vinyl strings were bunched\Ntogether and attached to the helmet...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.51,0:28:31.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the silhouette as seen through the shoji screen would\Nlook like the Suwa-style helmets of Takeda Shingen.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.02,0:28:37.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then Shigetsugu san, who has that armor used\Nin the festival in his room, is the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.27,0:28:39.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. Look over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.73,0:28:42.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those are the footprints from an unusual sandal.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.28,0:28:46.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They continue right up to the back gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.49,0:28:53.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then some outsider must have sneaked in and taken the\Narmor and used it to make that silhouette of Shingen.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.67,0:29:00.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or, someone from this house made those sandal\Nprints on purpose to make it look that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.67,0:29:03.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said something earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.63,0:29:06.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said, "Speaking of armor, they\Nhave one at Akira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s house too."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.01,0:29:10.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's some armor at the other house too?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.35,0:29:11.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.85,0:29:14.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said the Tatsuo family had a really magnificent one.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.52,0:29:19.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, we'll go over to the Tatsuo house.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.15,0:29:21.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha, you two stay here with the old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.36,0:29:26.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you already know this, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.16,0:29:30.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Keep your eyes on Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, since he\Nwas one of those looking for the buried gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.41,0:29:33.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd do that without you telling me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.20,0:29:33.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.91,0:29:35.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.83,0:29:37.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've been left behind again.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.92,0:29:41.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it's because he doesn't want to put you at risk, Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.34,0:29:46.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, how we're always experiencing dangerous\Nsituations and being targeted by criminals.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.93,0:29:49.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.76,0:29:54.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and after keeping you in suspense, he's going to\Ntell you the real story with a prideful look on his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.39,0:29:56.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi does that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.98,0:30:01.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, but in Shin'ichi's case, it's not because he likes me or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.32,0:30:05.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be as swift as the wind."
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.24,0:30:10.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You like him, don't you? That dark-skinned boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.16,0:30:12.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.37,0:30:17.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's OK to sit yourself down like a mountain and wait patiently.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.46,0:30:25.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But while your feelings are hot, another\Nway is to act swiftly, like the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.92,0:30:33.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you grow careless, before you can tell him your feelings,\Nthe other person might vanish right before your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.89,0:30:37.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because there are some things that can't be brought back.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.39,0:30:40.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like in my case.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.82,0:30:49.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's strange. It's strange, Kudo.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.28,0:30:53.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that thing in Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.53,0:30:55.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That gag.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.83,0:30:59.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was probably put on her to block her voice, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.33,0:31:03.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you wanted to make it seem like she committed\Nsuicide because she was afraid of Shingen's curse...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.92,0:31:05.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd normally take it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.51,0:31:08.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means there was some reason it couldn't be taken off...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.51,0:31:11.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or possibly it was left there on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.34,0:31:15.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if it was on purpose, why would the\Nculprit have done something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.89,0:31:18.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, she couldn't talk after she was dead, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.43,0:31:20.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it was a threat directed at someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.77,0:31:24.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meaning don't say anything and keep quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.11,0:31:32.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a really impressive suit of armor.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.99,0:31:36.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does the fact that it's red mean is from\NTakeda's "Akazonae"? (red armored warriors)
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.08,0:31:37.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.83,0:31:40.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is your family related to Takeda or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.62,0:31:44.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, my mother and I were big fans of Lord Shingen, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.46,0:31:46.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We spent a lot of money to get this.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.96,0:31:51.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both my late son Kouji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and Yoshirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} from the Torada family...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.55,0:31:53.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They really liked Shingen too.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.85,0:31:55.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They would come here often to look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.97,0:31:58.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My other son, Akira, wasn't like that though.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.77,0:32:05.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, even though they're both your sons, why do say "kun" when you\Nmention Kouji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, but you refer to Akira san without an honorific?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.40,0:32:10.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kouji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was the husband of my daughter, who was born after Akira.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.99,0:32:12.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He took our family name.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.49,0:32:17.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see, my daughter died in a traffic accident quite a long time ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.29,0:32:21.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And before they got married, Kouji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was Akira's classmate.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.33,0:32:25.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He used to come over to our house a lot, and\Nso just like in those days, I still use "kun."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.29,0:32:28.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of classmates...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.30,0:32:34.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both Yoshirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} from\Nthe Torada family were Akira's classmates too.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.18,0:32:38.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoshirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} were\Nclassmates even though they were brothers?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.01,0:32:44.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no. Yoshirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was the son of the elder sister\Nof Naonobu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the head of the Torada family.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.48,0:32:51.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard that his sister and her husband both died at an early age,\Nso he adopted him and raised them just like natural brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.49,0:32:54.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then that means that the three people who've died...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.16,0:32:58.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't related by blood to either the\NTorada family or to the Tatsuo family?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.53,0:33:02.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was Akira's wife also.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.79,0:33:06.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, that banner behind the armor...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.58,0:33:07.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.84,0:33:09.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a replica.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.38,0:33:12.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you read it, little boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.67,0:33:15.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be as quiet as the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.30,0:33:18.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be as quiet as the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.22,0:33:21.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Attack as fiercely as the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.39,0:33:24.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be immovable like the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.89,0:33:28.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the art of war as advocated a long time ago by Sun Tzu.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.07,0:33:31.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.57,0:33:35.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoshirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who as seriously injured\Nby the tornado and left to die was...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.57,0:33:37.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.66,0:33:43.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kouji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was tied up, buried in dirt piled\Nup like a mountain, and beaten to death was...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.04,0:33:45.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.33,0:33:51.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was left gagged in the middle\Nof the woods suspended from a tree was...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.67,0:33:52.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.05,0:33:54.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.97,0:33:59.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, our culprit is patterning himself after Takeda Shingen.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.55,0:34:02.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Making use of the strategy that he preferred...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.52,0:34:08.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Fuurinkazan.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.99,0:34:19.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fuurinkazan?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.99,0:34:23.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is patterning their crimes based on that?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.62,0:34:24.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.75,0:34:29.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Try and think back carefully about those three incidents in succession.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.58,0:34:35.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Start with the first case, where Torada Yoshirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nwas seriously injured by the tornado and left to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.80,0:34:37.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tornado is the "wind."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.76,0:34:41.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order words, the "wind" from "Be as swift as the wind."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.76,0:34:47.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next is the second case where Tatsuo Kouji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was\Ntied up, buried in the ground, and beaten to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.44,0:34:53.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That he was tied up and unable to move after being\Nburied in dirt piled like a mountain refers to...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.82,0:34:57.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "mountain" from "Be immovable like the mountain."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.28,0:35:02.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And earlier, the third case where Tatsuo Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nwas killed in the middle of the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.12,0:35:07.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The meaning behind the gag preventing her\Nfrom speaking and keeping her quiet was...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.79,0:35:13.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see now. The "forest" from "Be as quiet as the forest."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.21,0:35:19.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it looks like our serial murderer is\Npretty obsessed with Takeda Shingen.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.26,0:35:22.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why Takeda Shingen?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.14,0:35:26.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it to prevent them from digging up Shingen's buried gold after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.06,0:35:28.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.64,0:35:31.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is one thing we do know now though.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.40,0:35:35.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is still the "fire" (ka) character remaining in "Fuurinkazan."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.73,0:35:40.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means we can be certain that the culprit\Nis planning to take one other person's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.57,0:35:47.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, it could be the next target was one of those searching\Nfor the buried gold along with the three people who've died.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.70,0:35:49.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} or Akira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.91,0:35:52.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there's a high probability.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.75,0:35:57.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, it's possible that it just looks like that\Nand they may be targeting someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.51,0:36:00.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, at any rate, we'll be keeping watch here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.80,0:36:05.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You keep your eyes on the people\Nover there, particularly Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.64,0:36:06.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.60,0:36:10.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}. What does that mean, that "Fuurinkazan?"
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.06,0:36:13.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I've seen it used on TV and in the movies though.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.81,0:36:15.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? You don't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.07,0:36:26.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be as swift as the wind, be as silent as the forest, attack\Nas fiercely as the fire, be immovable like the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.45,0:36:30.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's one of the strategies that the great\Nmilitary strategist Sun Tzu conceived.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.08,0:36:34.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When an army moves, they are as swift as the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.88,0:36:37.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When they wait, they are as silent as the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.34,0:36:40.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When they attack, they are as fierce as fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.34,0:36:44.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When they decide to defend, they are immovable like a mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.18,0:36:51.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what Takeda Shingen, reputed to be the strongest\Nleader during the Sengoku, had written on his banners.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.56,0:36:53.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.14,0:36:54.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what Yui{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.44,0:36:59.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's OK to sit yourself down like a mountain and wait patiently.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.57,0:37:05.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But while your feelings are hot, another\Nway is to act swiftly, like the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.36,0:37:10.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I see. The "Fuurinkazan" strategy can be applied to love too.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.80,0:37:27.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.06,0:37:33.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you practice when you're upset over your wife's death...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.68,0:37:35.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You won't be able to concentrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.64,0:37:39.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's just that the festival is approaching,\Nand I can't neglect my training.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.86,0:37:44.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm putting all of my effort into being the horseback archery bowman.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.82,0:37:46.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what I swore to do at the grave of my senpai, Kai.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.95,0:37:51.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what my wife, Ayaka, would have wanted too.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.20,0:37:56.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, the reason I missed the target wasn't because I'm upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.08,0:37:59.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, that shows the target was shifted a bit, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.34,0:38:00.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.17,0:38:03.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who would so something strange like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.51,0:38:06.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's some people there behind the trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.51,0:38:10.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what are you doing? Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.68,0:38:11.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.97,0:38:14.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were probably guys from the neighboring village.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.98,0:38:18.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were trying to make me lose my self confidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.69,0:38:19.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why so?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.23,0:38:22.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the honor of their village is at stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.57,0:38:29.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The festival is an event that the two villages\Nhave conducted together for generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.07,0:38:34.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only one person becomes the bowman for the horseback archery\Ncontest, which is the number one highlight of the festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.62,0:38:39.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is to say, if they can ruin Akira san, the representative\Nof our village who won in the preliminary contest...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.88,0:38:43.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bowman from the other village will become the star of the festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.38,0:38:46.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They could brag about it for a whole year.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.59,0:38:51.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you count starting with Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, for more than 10 years the\Nbowman for the festival has been someone from our village.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.47,0:38:53.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happens during the preliminary contest?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.93,0:38:59.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ten targets are setup at even intervals on the\Ngrounds of the shrine, and we compete by hit ratio.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.60,0:39:02.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We keep on doing it until a winner is decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.77,0:39:03.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.90,0:39:08.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Six years ago, you and Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had both hit all the targets.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.36,0:39:13.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it was getting dark, the match was suspended until the next day.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.83,0:39:16.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how it was left when Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.41,0:39:20.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And one week later I discovered his body.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.92,0:39:21.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.25,0:39:26.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we had held the match on the following day, I would have lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.01,0:39:34.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When compared to my senpai, who after that tie match, said\Nhe was going to sweat it out a bit more at practice, I was...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.18,0:39:36.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So exhausted that I couldn't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.14,0:39:40.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He went to practice even though it was already getting dark?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.27,0:39:41.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.52,0:39:47.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As long as he knew the positions of the targets.\Nhe could have done it with his eyes closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.57,0:39:50.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he missed the target at his last festival, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.99,0:39:53.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was an underhanded trick perpetrated\Nby the people from the neighboring town.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.91,0:39:59.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They shifted the position of the target\Non purpose in order to embarrass him.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.58,0:40:07.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not knowing that, my father-in-law\NNaonobu got blazing mad at Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.76,0:40:10.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've sullied my honor!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.22,0:40:12.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did he mean, sullied?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.14,0:40:17.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems my father in law Naonobu was the one\Nwho taught Officer Kai horseback archery.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.68,0:40:21.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, my grandmother Shigeyo happened to be there...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.44,0:40:22.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And quarreled with him then.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.02,0:40:28.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone like you who's never once been chosen as the\Nbowman for the festival shouldn't act like you're a master.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.65,0:40:33.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In some way or another, everyone seems\Nto have some connection to that Kai guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.20,0:40:34.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.37,0:40:39.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that makes all of them suspects in these serial murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.29,0:40:45.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I examined the area surrounding the place where Tatsuo\NAyaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body was discovered carefully, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.75,0:40:49.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Except for the footprints of those who came\Nrushing there, the hoof marks from the horses...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.92,0:40:53.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the tracks of the tires from the\Nscooter and the car, there was nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.80,0:40:59.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In short, if we exclude you guys from the outside, the\Nonly ones who could feasibly be the culprit are...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.68,0:41:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those from the Torada family: Naonobu, Tatsue, Shigetsugu, and Yui.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.35,0:41:09.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or those from the Tatsuo family: Shigeyo,\NTamefumi, and Akira. Only those seven people.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.73,0:41:10.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are eight people.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.70,0:41:17.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your footprints and the marks from your\Ncane were there too, right, Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.99,0:41:20.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you can include me if you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.16,0:41:24.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Madam, you came here to get that horse, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.08,0:41:28.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, lead your dark bay back to the Torada house right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.67,0:41:32.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for you, take these kids with you and return to the Tatsuo house.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.80,0:41:36.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you return, tell this to the people in the house:
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.55,0:41:38.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The culprit is one of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.68,0:41:45.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Until I, Kansuke, arrive to take them away, they should stay\Nquietly in their houses and recite a prayer to the Buddha."
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.82,0:41:54.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't you call me by my name like you did in the old days...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.32,0:41:56.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.82,0:42:00.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but as for now, you're no longer my childhood friend Yui.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.58,0:42:04.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or my junior officer Uehara either.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.00,0:42:06.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're just the wife of a victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.25,0:42:10.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just one of my suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.84,0:42:12.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did he mean by "junior officer?"
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.71,0:42:15.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's a former police officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.01,0:42:19.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what I'm telling you!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.09,0:42:22.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have no memory of anyone who might be intending to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.14,0:42:25.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, but what is it that you've been doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.98,0:42:29.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I figure with all that's happened that I won't be\Nable to hunt for the treasure for a while...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.61,0:42:31.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I came here to get various documents and such.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.98,0:42:36.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's not here! The memo pad where I was\Nrecording the progress of the treasure hunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.61,0:42:39.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, then Akira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} must have it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.95,0:42:44.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, you and he are the only treasure hunters still left alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.66,0:42:47.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he's planning on keeping all the treasure for himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.29,0:42:49.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akira isn't the kind of person who would do something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.88,0:42:52.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's been my hero since we were classmates.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.80,0:42:56.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But people's hearts can change, Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.92,0:43:02.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, how can you know what someone bearing\Nthe blood of the Tatsuo family might be thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.68,0:43:06.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nonsense! Don't confuse him with your\Nown Torada family's prodigal son.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.02,0:43:11.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akira's been the bowman for the festival\Nfive years in a row! He's a samurai!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.23,0:43:12.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you here!?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.15,0:43:15.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We came looking for Akira.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.11,0:43:17.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We thought he might be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.69,0:43:24.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for Akira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Heiji told me over the phone that he finished\Nhis horseback archery practice and is on his way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.33,0:43:31.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well now, at any rate, let's all go back to our respective houses\Nfor the present and remain alert until this case has been settled.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.00,0:43:33.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You too, Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.92,0:43:36.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.05,0:43:38.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK, I guess we'll be heading off this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.59,0:43:41.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please be careful on the way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.39,0:43:46.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nobody's going to attack a horrible old mountain hag like her.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.52,0:43:50.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those words fit you perfectly too, you bald raccoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.89,0:43:55.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oops, now now. Didn't Shingen say this too?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.36,0:43:57.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Compassion is your ally; resentment is your enemy."
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.49,0:44:06.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be better here if both families put aside their\Ndisagreements and cooperate to resolve this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.58,0:44:13.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not for someone like you to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.04,0:44:17.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What you just said was Officer Kai's favorite phrase.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.92,0:44:22.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He often used those words to bring quarrels\Nbetween both families to a close.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.72,0:44:27.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That silly fool was a big fan of Shingen.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.69,0:44:34.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, so you'll be my wife when you grow up?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.65,0:44:40.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll have to let me off the hook on that,\Nor else Kansuke will be mad at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.70,0:44:44.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, please stop calling me "sensei"
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.70,0:44:47.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Despite the difference in age, you're my rival.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.41,0:44:50.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't mind if you call me Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-senpai{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.75,0:44:53.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Hattori...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.33,0:44:58.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would the culprit be patterning\Ntheir crimes after "Fuurinkazan?"
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.00,0:45:05.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it has something to do with how the three\Nvictims were all searching for Shingen's buried gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.05,0:45:10.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or possibly they might be trying to make us\Nthink that in order to hide their true motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.60,0:45:16.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, you know, Yoshirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s being swallowed\Nup by that tornado was completely by chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.15,0:45:20.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, the fact that they had the corpse of\Nthe centipede already prepared would mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.82,0:45:25.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit had been planning to kill\Nthose three for some time before that.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.82,0:45:34.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, the thing that bothers me is that matter about Yoshirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Kouji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} saying they were going to see that Detective Yamato.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.58,0:45:40.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What has me is how Ayaka san suddenly was so startled\Nwhen she heard about Shingen's armored helmet.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.71,0:45:43.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of being bothered, there's one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.05,0:45:43.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.59,0:45:47.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Officer Kai's death by falling.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.84,0:45:52.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, we still have the remaining\Ncharacter "fire" from "Fuurinkazan."
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.14,0:45:59.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will the next target be Akira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} or—
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.36,0:46:05.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.70,0:46:07.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sounded like thunder.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.66,0:46:11.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji! Something terrible has happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.45,0:46:13.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's is it, Kazuha?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.08,0:46:14.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.50,0:46:16.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a huge noise, and when I turned around...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.04,0:46:18.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.83,0:46:22.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when we went back to the railroad crossing\Nto look for him, the train had stopped...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.71,0:46:25.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And in front of the train...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.88,0:46:29.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a collapsed person on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.72,0:46:31.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a person on fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.85,0:46:34.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I think it could be Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.47,0:46:37.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait right there! I'll be there as soon as possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.69,0:46:42.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"As fierce as the fife," huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.69,0:48:08.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.19,0:48:09.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eye Shadow
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.07,0:48:11.57,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next time we start at 7:00 PM too.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.61,0:48:14.12,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Conan keeps on confronting puzzling cases. Hooray!
